HEADWORD: Hoggerel
<hw>Hog"ger*el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the same
source as <ets>hog</ets>; prob. orig., a sheep clipped the first year.
See <er>Hog</er>.]</ety> <def>A sheep of the second year.
<altsp>[Written also <asp>hogrel</asp>.]</altsp>
<xex>Ash</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

